Here are the simple steps to do it entirely through your web browser:

🚀 Step-by-Step: Host your Maquette on GitHub for Free
1. Create a Repository
Go to github.com and log into your account.

In the top-right corner, click the + icon and select New repository.

Name your repository (for example: stromboli-maquette).

Crucial Step: Set the visibility to Public (if it is private, the free hosting feature won't work).

Check the box that says Add a README file.

Click the green Create repository button at the bottom.

2. Upload your index.html
Inside your new repository, look at the top right of the file section and click Add file → Upload files.

Drag and drop your index.html file directly into the box.

Scroll down to the bottom of the page and click the green Commit changes button.

3. Turn on the Live Link (GitHub Pages)
At the top menu of your repository, click on the ⚙️ Settings tab.

Look at the left sidebar, find the Code and automation section, and click on Pages.

Under Build and deployment → Source, make sure it says Deploy from a branch.

Under Branch, change it from None to main (or master), leave the folder as / (root), and click Save.

🔗 Getting Your Link
Give GitHub about 1 to 2 minutes to process the file. Refresh your page, and at the top of that same Pages settings screen, you will see a message like this:

"Your site is live at: https://yourusername.github.io/stromboli-maquette/"

