Instead of forcing the browser to jump between different files (like about.html or cafe.html), you include all your pages inside separate container blocks (<div> panels) directly inside the same file. Then, you use a tiny, clean JavaScript state manager script at the bottom to instantly show and hide them as the user clicks through the menu items!

This approach is highly recommended for interactive mockups because it means you only have to maintain, upload, and update one single file on GitHub, and the links switch between pages instantaneously with zero load times.

